Keithley 2450 SourceMeter was employed to acquire resistance signals of hydrogels under different deformations. Two copper wires acting as electrodes were connected to the both ends of hydrogels and the SourceMeter. Gauge factor (GF) was adopted to evaluate the strain sensitivity of the hydrogel sensor. GF was defined as follows:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
